SIMPLE: articulately
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Articulately
<hw>Ar*tic"u*late*ly</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>After the manner, or in the form, of a joint.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Article by article; in distinct particulars; in
detail; definitely.</def> <rj><au>Paley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I had <qex>articulately</qex> set down in writing our points.</q>
<rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>With distinct utterance of the separate
sounds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Articulateness</ent>⟦br⟧
